    longDescription: "Figma is a cloud-native, real-time collaborative UI/UX design and prototyping platform primarily used by product designers, UX researchers, developers, and cross-functional teams to co-create interfaces, build interactive prototypes, and establish design systems at scale. Its core value proposition centers on eliminating version control friction, enabling synchronous editing, and bridging design-to-development handoff via developer-friendly inspect modes and auto-generated code snippets. Target users include startups, enterprise design teams (e.g., Microsoft, Airbnb), and agencies seeking scalable, browser-accessible workflows without local software dependencies. Key differentiators include its unified design-dev-prototype environment, robust plugin ecosystem (over 6,500 plugins as of 2024), vector network engine for precision editing, and industry-leading collaboration features like multiplayer cursors and comment threading — all contributing to a 92% user satisfaction rate for team collaboration (G2 Fall 2023 Grid Report). Figma’s web-first architecture enables 98% uptime and sub-100ms latency for real-time edits across 150+ countries. It supports macOS, Windows, Linux, and iPadOS with offline mode limited to recent files. Ratings sourced from G2.",
